     <br>
<br>
He is no match for the enchanter, or rather her servant. With one feeble blast from the skeleton, Jobober tears into the it with a vengence. With a clank of bones, the offending creature is dead and Jobober camly walks back to Alleusion's side.<br>
     <br>
<br>
&quot;Nice, Jobober,&quot; Alleusion says wearily, &quot;let's hope this helps accomplish our goals.&quot;<br>
     <br>
<br>
Once more the elf settles back into the sand, rumaging through her packs to find something to occupy her time. Off to her right she can hear the battle cries of the young as they test their might against the orcs that roam the desert. Further out, past a cool lake, float menacing spectres, just waiting and watching for someone to come too close. Alleusion cleared her mind and settled down to some meditation when she heard the death cry of an Iksar. <br>
     <br>
<br>
That in itself would not be enough to break her from her thoughts. But this was a different cry. To the trained elf's ear, this was a false cry...to the weak creatures of the desert, it was a cry saying they had won again.<br>
     <br>
<br>
&quot;Phobose, you've come to keep me company.&quot; Alleusion said with a hint of impatience in her voice. &quot;Jobober is nice, but he doesn't talk much.&quot;<br>
     <br>
<br>
Not moving from his spot in the sand, the iskar sighed. &quot;Yes, and neither do I.&quot; Jumping up and dusting the offending sand from his clothes, Phobose ran off, mindlessly slaughtering anything that dared cross his path.<br>
     <br>
<br>
Alleusion rolled her eyes. She didn't understand how someone covered in a thick hide of scales could move about so nimbly in the fierce heat. Standing slowly, willing the dust to remove itself from her clothes, Alleusion brought her pale hand up to shade her eyes. Off to the east she could see a few madmen, crazed eyes glazed over from the desert heat. Waving her hand toward them, she called to them with the barking of tashania, forcing them to come after her. Standing under their weak onslaught, letting her sheilded skin absorb the damage while Jobober finished them off.<br>
     <br>
<br>
Feeling the earth rumble under her feet, Alleusion turned toward the sound that could only mean one thing. Facing north, out of the sun, she saw the turbaned head of a sand giant peeking out over a dune. Taking off towards the giant, Alleusion stood on the crest of the dune and watched Phobose take him down.<br>
     <br>
<br>
&quot;Impressive,&quot; she said, &quot;but that's not him is it?&quot;<br>
     <br>
<br>
&quot;No, Alleusion, that was not the one you were looking for.&quot; Phobose stated, not even out of breath from his destruction of the giant.<br>
     <br>
<br>
Settling down once again, Alleusion called creatures to her, letting her faithful pet destroy them one by one. I'm sorry, she thought as a particularly difficult skeleton met his demise, but you must die. Nothing personal you understand, but if I want my giant to come, I must kill his minions.<br>
     <br>
<br>
And into the night she continued. Killing undead, orcs, and madmen, all random, all in an attempt at mass destruction. As the sun faded, and the sands cooled, Alleusion gained momentum, until the morrow, when the sun would once again plague the land. Until tomorrow she thought, wondering if what she sought, would finally be hers. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/ualleusion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alleusion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/24/02 5:23:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/umalikyemadonemoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MalikyeMadoneMoon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~malikye/Malikye4.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lor Mani Friend</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#333333>(6/26/02 10:03:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/flormani79848frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~malikye/Malikye4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oasis</span><hr size=1> want to start camping OA every night IM on?  Ill be happy to Alle just lemme know  <p>Malikye
